<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph id="IAS32_AG38B" base="F17320338"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>AG38B</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 32"/><data name="paranum" value="AG38B"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS32_P0582">To meet the criterion in <xref id="IAS32_X0709" base="F19320833" href="IAS32_42.dita#IAS32_42/IAS32_42_V2">paragraph 42(a)</xref>, an entity must currently have a legally enforceable right of set‑off. This means that the right of set‑off:</p><ol outputclass="static" id="IAS32_L0052" base="F17320339" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IAS32_P0583" base="F17320341">must not be contingent on a future event; and</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IAS32_P0584" base="F17320343">must be legally enforceable in all of the following circumstances:</p> <ol outputclass="static" id="IAS32_L0053" base="F17320344" type="lower-roman"><li><li_value>(i)</li_value> <p id="IAS32_P0585" base="F17320346">the normal course of business;</p></li><li><li_value>(ii)</li_value> <p id="IAS32_P0586" base="F17320348">the event of default; and</p></li><li><li_value>(iii)</li_value> <p id="IAS32_P0587" base="F17320350">the event of insolvency or bankruptcy</p></li></ol> <p id="IAS32_P0588" base="F17320351">of the entity and all of the counterparties.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>